# NOTE: this file is retained for reference only.  The current
# F9T-to-TCP bridge uses socat (see deploy/systemd/f9t-tcp-bridge-ptpmon.service),
# not str2str.
#
# RTKLIB's str2str does not handle kernel GNSS char devices well:
#   - `serial://` calls termios.tcgetattr() which returns EINVAL on
#     /dev/gnss* (kernel GNSS char devices are not ttys).
#   - `file://` opens the device but stays at "(1) waiting" with 0 bps
#     output — RTKLIB's file mode expects a seekable regular file,
#     not a live char-device stream.
#
# socat handles both cleanly via its FILE address.  See the systemd
# unit for the canonical command.  This template stays in the repo
# in case str2str becomes useful later (RTCM filtering, format
# conversion to RINEX via convbin, etc.) on a different transport.
#
# Original template preserved below for reference:
#
# -in file:///dev/gnss0
# -out tcpsvr://:2101
# -t 5
